t() to create a Put operation (line 87)\n   - Uses Txn().If().Then().Commit() to conditionally write to etcd\n\n7. etcd Client Operation (etcd-io/etcd:client/v3/op.go)\n   - OpPut() function (line 271) creates an Op struct with type tPut and encodes the key-value pair\n   - The actual write is executed via the KV Txn interface which connects to the etcd server\n\nCodec Serialization:\n- The runtime.Codec is configured in kubernetes/kubernetes:staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/storagebackend/config.go (ConfigForResource struct, line 67)\n- This codec handles the serialization of Go runtime objects to bytes before storage\n- Codec is typically initialized with a specific GroupVersion that determines how Pods are serialized (e.g., core/v1)\n\nKey Flow Summary:\nHTTP PUT request → REST handler → genericregistry.Store.Create() → etcd3 Store.Create() → Codec.Encode() → Transformer.TransformToStorage() → etcd client OptimisticPut → etcd KV.Txn().Put() → etcd server"
